   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Regional CL</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- The Project will allow Banco Regional to provide its SME clients access to funding with longer maturities enabling them to undertake capital investments at longer tenors and attractive costs;
- Given the nationwide presence of the Bank, the Project will contribute to rural economic development while reaching the BOP in rural areas;
- Due to the maximum average sub-loan size of US$1 million, the facility will be 100% used to finance SMEs;
- IFC will enhance its support to the expansion of a leading financial institution in the Paraguayan system.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed investment involves supporting Banco Regional S.A.E.C.A. (Banco Regional or the Bank) in providing medium- and long-term financing to Paraguayan SMEs.

The primary objective of the Project is to support an existing client of IFC with a strong focus in the agribusiness sector, but that intends to expand into other economic sectors. By enhancing access to finance for SMEs (a key driver of the economic activity in Paraguay), the proposed investment will enable IFC to consolidate its programmatic approach in the local financial sector.</narrative>
  </description>
